subSubSection.paragraph:
Mesosoma.
Length of mesosoma 1.35 × as long as high (81: 60) (
Fig. 16
); propleuron sparsely crenulate; precoxal sulcus shallowly depressed; mesopleuron shiny and largely smooth; metapleuron with sparse fine punctures; mesoscutum distinctly protruding above pronotum, largely smooth with sparse fine punctures; notauli narrow and deep anteriorly, with a deep median depression posteriorly between notauli (
Fig. 15
); scutellar sulcus 0.7 × as long as scutellum (8: 12) with one carina; scutellum smooth; propodeum rugose without trace of areola.
